## Setup Instructions

### 1ï¸âƒ£ Backend Setup

```bash
# Navigate to backend folder
cd backend

# Install dependencies
npm install

# Create a .env file with content:
# PORT=5000
# API_KEY=your_api_key_here  (if applicable)

# Start backend server
npm start
Backend runs at: http://localhost:5000
Test API endpoint: http://localhost:5000/api/analyze (POST JSON)

2ï¸âƒ£ Frontend Setup
bash
Copy code
# Navigate to frontend folder
cd ../frontend

# Install dependencies
npm install

# Create .env.local file with content:
# VITE_API_URL=http://localhost:5000

# Run frontend in development mode
npm run dev
Open http://localhost:5173 in your browser.
Hot-reloading works for development.

bash
Copy code
# Build frontend for production
npm run build

# Install serve globally (if not installed)
npm install -g serve

# Serve the production build
serve -s dist
Access production version at http://localhost:3000.

3ï¸âƒ£ Restart Commands
bash
Copy code
# Backend
cd backend
npm start

# Frontend (dev mode)
cd ../frontend
npm run dev

# Frontend (production serve)
cd frontend
serve -s dist


4ï¸âƒ£ Common Issues & Fixes
Blank page or runtime errors:

Check browser console for errors.

Ensure .env.local contains correct VITE_API_URL.

Ensure all CSS braces are closed (PostCSS errors can break the page).

Port conflicts:

Backend default: 5000

Frontend dev default: 5173

Use PORT environment variable to change ports.

